metadata.name: Balanced #126
Rough Cuts #271
metadata.description:
Abstract generative artwork that explores composition and form by cutting canvas with straight lines. Coded brushwork gives a real-painting look to each piece.

Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, July, 2022.

metadata.name: Sketch D #24
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch D (Disruption). The grid is broken. The color palette from Sketches A, B, and C remains. Most outputs are simply single colors or black and white. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

Press the spacebar to see the unDisturbed structure.

metadata.description: "You take the blue pill... the story ends, you wake up in your bed and believe whatever you want to believe. You take the red pill... you stay in Wonderland, and I show you how deep the rabbit hole goes"

metadata.name: Stones and Sticks #36
metadata.description:
In this project I explore the technique for creating figures, lights, and shades by only using the line primitive. I imagine a primitive world, a distant planet where life can begin again or has just been swept away by some deadly wind. Stones and sticks the only means for building and creating useful tools, just like in this computer-generated image.
-	Hit ‘s’ to save a hi res (5683x3072) png file
-	Dark, Light and Gold modes

metadata.description:
➡️ This is for the Morixels family and benefits those who own at least one of the Morixels tokens ⬅️

If you have a minimum of 1 NFTs from Morixels even Colabs or Mega Colab
We whitelist you for having a minimum of 1 Morixels Goose

You don't have Morixels?

Don't worry you can buy from the primary or the secondary market 👇

https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/morixels-mans


The Morixels Goose are unique Random Generated 1000 PFP NFTs.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 25 by 25 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution.
The number of Traits in this collection is 9 (168 layers) and it has the ability to make 42,674,688,000 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.description:
Desertification and drought.
What remain from the old buildings now look like ghosts.
There is no life here.
It is the same everywhere. 
There is no future.

2000 x 2000 px

metadata.name: Притяжение #46
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

——————

Rendering takes around 20 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.

hrunz. — Aug. 2022.
